          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and bake the shortbread, 20 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 170°C fan. Grease and line a 20 x 20 cm square tin. Rub the cold {{unsalted-butter}} into the {{plain-flour}}, {{icing-sugar}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs. Press firmly and evenly into the base of the tin. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes until the shortbread is pale golden. Do not turn off the oven; reduce to 160°C.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour the curd and finish baking, 22 to 25 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "While the base bakes, whisk the {{eggs}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{lemon-juice}}, {{lemon}} zest, and {{plain-flour}} together until smooth. As soon as the shortbread comes out of the oven, pour the curd evenly over the hot base. Bake at 160°C for 22 to 25 minutes until the curd is just set and does not wobble when shaken. Cool in the tin to room temperature, then refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Dust with {{icing-sugar}} and cut into 16 bars.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
